The use of SINR levels and interference suggests that the paper is related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The analysis of the optimal power vector in large, random networks suggests that the paper may also be related to statistical inference (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of random erasures and the analysis of the tails of the eigenvalue distribution suggest that the paper may also be related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
